events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 28 points, 10 assists and a season-high 12 rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets beat San Antonio 120-110 on Wednesday night to send the Spurs into the NBA All-Star break with a franchise-record 14-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball has triple-double, Hornets hand Spurs 14th loss in row

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield made six 3-pointers in the second half and finished with 27 points, helping the Indiana Pacers rally from a 24-point deficit after the first quarter and defeat the Chicago Bulls 117-113 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield helps Pacers rally from 24 down to beat Bulls 117-113

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 29 points — including the 10,000th of his career — and the Philadelphia 76ers survived a rocky second half to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 118-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 29 points, helps 76ers snap Cavaliers' win streak

events.name: New York Knicks at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson is on quite a streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 28, Randle 25, Knicks rout Hawks 122-101

headlines.description: — The Celtics got back their offensive and defensive spark plugs. Together, they gave Boston the jolt it needed to head into the All-Star break on track to accomplish all its goals this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's 38 points help Celtics roll past Pistons 127-109

headlines.description: — In his third game since arriving in the Kevin Durant trade, Mikal Bridges had an electrifying scoring stretch to rival even the superstar he replaced.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mikal Bridges scores career-high 45, Nets beat Heat 116-105

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson had 26 points, nine rebounds and four blocks and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Utah Jazz 117-111 on Wednesday night in the last game for both teams before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Bane lead Grizzlies over Jazz, 117-111

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Oklahoma City Thunder created the kind of momentum they wanted to take into the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 29, helps Thunder dominate Rockets

headlines.description: — Reserve Jeff Green scored a season-high 24 points, Nikola Jokic notched his 21st triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets headed into the All-Star break with a 118-109 victory over the short-handed Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green helps Nuggets go into break with 118-109 win over Mavs

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 21 points in his first game since becoming the NBA’s career scoring leader, and Anthony Davis had 28 points, 10 rebounds and five assists in the new-look Los Angeles Lakers' 120-102 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron, Anthony Davis get new-look Lakers past Pelicans
